Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.66,0:00:23.07,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A brave heart and incredible deductions,\Na rhythm that jumps to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.37,0:00:24.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mystery of the pottery classroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.07,0:00:26.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What could be written on that cup?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:28.54,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeing the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.77,0:00:30.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A kid with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.44,0:00:32.58,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is... Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.65,0:01:44.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran joined Sonoko, who was attending her pottery class.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.78,0:01:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, good work. Yours looks very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.72,0:01:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.29,0:01:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.39,0:01:54.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does anybody know this boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.49,0:01:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.13,0:01:58.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I followed Ran to the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:04.74,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Muneyuki Mino (62)\NCraftsman
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:04.74,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The teacher of that class is Muneyuki Mino{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.14,0:02:09.74,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Kikuyo Kasama (29)\NMuneyuki's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.74,0:02:08.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and his assistant is Kazama Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.81,0:02:15.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, we met Mino Muneyuki's son-in-law, Mino Moto{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.35,0:02:16.92,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Mino Moto (31)\NBusinessman (Muneyuki's inheritor)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.25,0:02:20.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, Moto{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} suddenly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.89,0:02:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only place we haven't looked yet is this storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.96,0:02:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Look! Look, at the bottom of the closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.56,0:02:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.40,0:02:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this an apron for the pottery class?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.04,0:02:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.65,0:02:49.05,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Can you hear me, Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.15,0:02:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.95,0:02:55.32,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Moto{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} was killed, and the murderer\Nhas to be one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:02:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:02:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.02,0:03:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my cup! Don't you think it's pretty good?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:03:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... You really did a good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, boy, it seems as though you are a little bit confused...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.73,0:03:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're trying to hide something\Nbig, or you're facing a big decision...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I right? Because clay never lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.65,0:03:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're amazing, sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.98,0:03:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, you should think about your own problems\Nbefore you think about the problems of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.16,0:03:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who made this cup!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.70,0:03:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were searching the drawers earlier,\NI took your cup and switched it with mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.00,0:03:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you'd know the difference between the two cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if this is your cup, doesn't that mean\Nthat you're hiding something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you're hiding something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.19,0:04:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.73,0:04:12.43,Title,Sign,0,0,0,,The Murderous Pottery Class\N(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.71,0:04:23.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}T-This boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.81,0:04:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there an ink pen anywhere around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.95,0:04:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you, I'll return it as soon as I finish up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.99,0:04:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, thanks again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the Inspector asked me to\Nescort you to the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.07,0:04:49.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.67,0:04:51.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mino{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-sensei{\r\be10} is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:56.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've figured out the trick he used for his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.64,0:04:58.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But when we weren't looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.58,0:05:00.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}he hid the evidence somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:06.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But since he is still in possession of the scissors,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.89,0:05:09.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the evidence hasn't been destroyed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.59,0:05:10.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It is still around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:13.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn! Where could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:18.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe there is something the murderer hasn't\Naccounted for... another piece of evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.16,0:05:19.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.43,0:05:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.44,0:05:25.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Necktie?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:28.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.24,0:05:29.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.21,0:05:32.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I finally figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.91,0:05:35.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The evidence that no one noticed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:38.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The craftsman's mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.82,0:05:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been confirmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.56,0:05:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, that was not the only thing we found out...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, insurance...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.30,0:06:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazama Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it seems you are in a lot of debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.31,0:06:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah. I've recently bought a new house, so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.38,0:06:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing. I'm just curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.08,0:06:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the victim set up life insurance one week ago with you as the inheritor and it is equal to the amount you owe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.66,0:06:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.03,0:06:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, you came to this room in order\Nto get the first-aid kit for Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.57,0:06:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you weren't the killer, then you\Nwould've seen the victim's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.74,0:06:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already told you! I only opened the closet,\Nand at that time there was nothing there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.74,0:06:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, it didn't take me long\Nto come here and go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.65,0:06:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I kill him during that short period of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You offered to get Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} the first-aid kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.46,0:06:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is possible that you went and\Nhid the body during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.00,0:07:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to slow down the actual discovery of the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.97,0:07:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it is possible to purposely go to the closet and get the first\Naid kit, but accidentally left Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s apron sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.51,0:07:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong! I didn't kill anybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.05,0:07:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't hide this any longer, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was searching for Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and found her\Nin this room, grabbing Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} by the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.30,0:07:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. She said that she was helping him change\Nhis clothes, but it sure didn't look that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.71,0:07:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's wrong! It was only a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's finish this at the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.78,0:07:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything wrong, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:08:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know how every time we try to take someone to the police station, we always hear a weird sound that stops us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.73,0:08:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like "Myaaa" or "Fouhitoo".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.40,0:08:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean Detective Mouri, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.33,0:08:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's okay today, he's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.30,0:08:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.58,0:08:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This girl does the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.98,0:08:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really disappoint me, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.46,0:08:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.92,0:08:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you noticed yet? The victim's sleeves\Nwere folded at different lengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.83,0:08:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means that he was killed during the\Ntime he was changing his clothes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.74,0:08:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning, {\i1}that person{\i0} is the only one who\Ncould have committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.94,0:08:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}T-That person{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.48,0:08:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.71,0:08:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.01,0:08:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That person{\i0} came into the storage room a few moments\Nbefore Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} finished putting on his apron.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.55,0:09:01.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That person{\i0} then sent Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to help the students,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.99,0:09:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,leaving him alone with the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.19,0:09:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That person{\i0} is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, we noticed the difference\Nin lengths of his sleeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.17,0:09:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he has an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.14,0:09:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran said that the apron wasn't sticking\Nout after Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.85,0:09:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he stayed with you the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.35,0:09:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, just before the victim was\Nfound, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} opened the closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still don't know if she is the murderer or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.76,0:09:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She should have screamed the moment she saw\NMoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body, if she wasn't the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't some magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.23,0:09:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could the victim's body be placed in\Nthat closet without anybody noticing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.61,0:09:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this really is a magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.54,0:10:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} used Ran and Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nas his assistants in the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body appear in a closet\Nwhen nothing was supposed to be in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.82,0:10:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He used me and Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's quit talking, and prove that what I'm saying is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... Let's have Officer Takagi be the assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.67,0:10:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.08,0:10:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, this closet is empty, and completely\Nvoid of any mechanical object or trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please check that there's nothing\Nat the bottom of the closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.72,0:10:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please open the closet's right door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.09,0:10:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing inside, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.43,0:10:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. There is nothing unusual inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-There's a cloth sticking out from the bottom of the closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.77,0:11:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird, I didn't notice anything before I opened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.81,0:11:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see, the door's back-side!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.02,0:11:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the handkerchief that I asked Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to put there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} most likely taped the apron\Nto the closet's back-door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.13,0:11:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then closed the door, making sure it remained hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.04,0:11:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when someone opens the door, the cloth is pulled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.71,0:11:42.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, when someone closes the door, the cloth\Nis stuck out, and stays outside the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} intentionally dropped\Nthe plate in front of the closet,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.82,0:11:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and had Ran pick up the broken pieces so\Nshe noticed nothing was sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.43,0:11:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he said that he cut himself to make Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nopen the closet to get the first-aid kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.76,0:12:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After opening the door, the apron fell\Nout, putting his trap into effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh I see. The body was in the closet, even\Nbefore Ran cleaned up the broken plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.11,0:12:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what was meant by using a handkerchief, is that he\Nused the same method, except with a piece of apron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.32,0:12:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had noticed the piece of apron\Nsticking out after having closed the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.66,0:12:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When someone is injured, do you think anyone would\Nbe interested in looking at the door's backside?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or even be facing the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.23,0:12:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, where was the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.10,0:12:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the body fell when the closet was opened, this means\Nthat it was placed at the door's backside, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.24,0:12:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible that Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wouldn't notice\Nthat after getting the first-aid kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.08,0:12:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'll figure it out for yourself, if we\Ntry to open the closet one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.15,0:12:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this time, open both doors at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.65,0:12:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-Both doors?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.16,0:13:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A mop?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.06,0:13:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wasn't there when I opened the door before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.40,0:13:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.27,0:13:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trick is pretty easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.87,0:13:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, tie a rope on the mop's head in such a way\Nthat the rope is long and ends with a knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then tie the rope around the left hanger-bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.68,0:13:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Placing the mop, so that it is tilting towards the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.69,0:13:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, put the knot above the left door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.69,0:13:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doors are then closed simultaneously,\Nwith the knot sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.46,0:13:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once the right door opens, the mop cannot be\Nseen because it is hidden behind the clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.17,0:13:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, if you open both doors together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The knot will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.71,0:13:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which causes the mop to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.71,0:13:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This mop represents Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.48,0:13:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the rope can be replaced with his necktie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the knot can then be replaced with...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.32,0:14:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.52,0:14:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The necktie pin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.22,0:14:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.89,0:14:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will become more clear once\Nyou look at Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s necktie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the pin was on so low was to be\Nat the appropriate length for this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.57,0:14:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the reason why the necktie pin hole is so large,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.41,0:14:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is because of Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s weight pulling down on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But wouldn't the necktie pin and the necktie, sticking out of the upper part of the door, be easy for someone to notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.05,0:14:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you fold the part sticking out and slide it\Nback into the door, no one would notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.09,0:14:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, where is the piece of apron hidden?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.63,0:14:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we arrived here, we didn't find anything\Nsimilar to what you mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, he found the body with his students there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.11,0:14:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't possible to recover a thing like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.51,0:15:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.68,0:15:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he went and sat to the right side of Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he could have reached for the piece of apron, which\Nwould be behind him, take it, and hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he pulled hard enough, the tape on it would come\Noff, and the piece of apron would be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.43,0:15:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, when the door is closed, the apron can easily be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.17,0:15:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once the door opens halfway, the piece of apron\Ngets hidden until the door is completely open.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} simply took the piece\Nof apron and hid it in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.55,0:15:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:45.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you're saying that if we searched his\Npockets, we'd find the piece of apron?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.99,0:15:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, this is nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.16,0:15:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, as you can see, there's nothing in my pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.80,0:15:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.07,0:16:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably hid it in the bathroom, before the police\Narrived. So, as they were checking the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.94,0:16:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.18,0:16:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} saw Mino{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} searching for a pair of scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.71,0:16:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was ready to cut the apron into pieces,\Nand flush them down the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, Takagi, check that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.22,0:16:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nonsense. It doesn't matter where it's found.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.23,0:16:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like anyone saw me trying to hide something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, it is possible that anyone\Ncould have done this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.60,0:16:34.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we found the apron, the killer would\Nnot be the one in possession of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.64,0:16:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it can't be used as proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.61,0:16:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Sensei, there is a piece of concrete evidence that\Nproves that you were the one who did this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on the opposite side of the necktie, worn by Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.63,0:16:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.56,0:17:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nail marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.40,0:17:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, those are the marks left by the clay on Sensei's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finding these marks makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, Sensei was making a cup next to Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.31,0:17:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, looking at the location of the necktie pin,\Nthe necktie was barely long enough for the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.22,0:17:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to set the trick up, you would\Nhave to set the necktie pin in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.29,0:17:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once it is in place, you have to grab\Nthe end of the necktie, and pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.60,0:17:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you made two mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first was that you didn't wear gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.87,0:17:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second, is that you used the necktie\Nto hang the victim's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.78,0:17:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had you worn gloves, you wouldn't have\Nleft any traces of clay on the necktie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.42,0:17:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, had you used a rope instead of the necktie,\Nyou wouldn't have left any fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.56,0:18:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now what do you have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.53,0:18:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't like wearing gloves. I prefer touching\Nthings and feeling how they really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.10,0:18:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That necktie was a gift my daughter\Nsent him with all her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.68,0:18:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a Christmas present.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.38,0:18:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the person who put that necktie\Nin the bag with the card was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.55,0:18:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was me. I saw him thinking it was a present from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.19,0:18:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I wanted was to release my daughter's grudge,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.30,0:18:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by throwing the blame on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started suspecting your affair with him when\Nthe truck hit my daughter two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was three days after Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.51,0:18:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I went to my daughter's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found a necktie inside the trash-can, still inside the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.76,0:19:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was put there by mistake, so\NI went to the airport to give it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.10,0:19:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to give it to the man, who I thought should\Nbe grieving due to the recent death of his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.80,0:19:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what I saw at the airport was nothing\Nlike sadness towards his loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.34,0:19:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a person talking and laughing\Nwhile holding Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.78,0:19:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, I realized that my daughter\Nwasn't killed by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She actually found out about the\Naffair, and so she killed herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.10,0:19:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm surprised you knew this was for Moto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.34,0:19:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know it wasn't for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.01,0:20:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that because...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.68,0:20:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:07.99,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Beige?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.45,0:20:11.69,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't you think that that color is\Ntoo dark for Moto{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s taste?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.06,0:20:16.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, it's good. I like beige, and I want\Nhim to look just like you, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.56,0:20:20.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Beige is the color of clay. It's your favorite\Ncolor, isn't that right, father?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.84,0:20:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because... Just call it a father's instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.80,0:22:06.60,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Three Days Later
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.84,0:22:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got a letter from Kyoukogu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.48,0:22:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure don't look happy about it, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.08,0:22:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of this, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.98,0:22:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is he using it as a vase?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.99,0:22:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's mistook it for a flower pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.42,0:22:26.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.26,0:22:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you? Did you send yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.26,0:22:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or did you go through all that trouble, just to hide it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.34,0:22:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sort of messed up, so I decided not to send it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.17,0:22:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're out of chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.41,0:22:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.54,0:22:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you, but could you\Ngo get some chips from my desk?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.78,0:22:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.39,0:23:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? A pen-holder?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.29,0:23:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This reminds me of something...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.46,0:23:05.43,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Super Stupid Case Fanatic
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.19,0:23:05.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.96,0:23:08.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see, that's the cup Ran made.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.57,0:23:12.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Makes sense that she didn't send something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.87,0:23:18.31,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,I'm waiting for you ♡
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.77,0:23:17.67,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.01,0:23:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.68,0:23:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get the chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.32,0:23:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.32,0:23:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} seems in a very good mood today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.26,0:23:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's really strange.
